  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Twin Rooms</strong> are around 20m² sleep two people. These rooms have a shower, and are available for sole occupancy for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Twin Rooms With Balcony</strong> are around 22m² and sleep two to four (with either a single or bunk bed as the extra bed, depending on occupancy - extra beds suitable for children aged 12 and under). These rooms have a bath with showerhead.</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites</strong> are around 28m² and sleep two to three (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have a balcony and bath with showerhead.</p>
<p><strong>Two Room Suites</strong> are around 34m² and sleep two to four people (extra beds are single beds). These suites have two rooms with an interconnecting door, a balcony and a shared bathroom (with bath and showerhead).</p>
<p><strong>Single Rooms</strong> are around 15m² and have a shower. These rooms are under the eaves.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bathrobes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>2pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. CHF3.60 per person per night is payable locally (children aged 6-15 years pay a reduced rate of CHF2.50 per person per night, and guests aged 5 and under are exempt)</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Steps into property:<strong> 0</strong></li>
<li>Adapted rooms: <strong>1</strong> (room has walk-in shower but no other adaptations)</li>
<li>All public areas are on the flat</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
